# Infrastructure Monitoring with Prometheus and Node Exporter

## Project Overview

This project demonstrates the setup of a monitoring and observability stack using Prometheus and Node Exporter.

Prometheus was configured to scrape metrics exposed by Node Exporter and monitor system resources such as CPU, memory, filesystem, and network usage.

## Architecture

Node Exporter (Port 9100)
        ↓
Prometheus (Port 9090)
        ↓
PromQL Queries & Monitoring

## Components

- Prometheus
- Node Exporter
- PromQL

## Monitoring Workflow

1. Node Exporter exposes host metrics on port 9100.
2. Prometheus scrapes metrics every 15 seconds.
3. Metrics are stored in Prometheus TSDB.
4. PromQL is used to query and visualize metrics.

## Validation

Verified the setup by:

- Confirming Prometheus target status
- Confirming Node Exporter target status
- Running PromQL queries
- Checking metric collection

